Data Mining Framework for Association Rules & Analytics
       Project Overview

This project presents the design and implementation of a comprehensive data mining framework integrating multiple analytical techniques, including association rules, classification, regression, and clustering. The goal is to extract meaningful insights from real-world datasets across different domains such as e-commerce, healthcare, and housing.

       Objectives
Implement and compare key data mining algorithms
Optimize model performance using tuning and evaluation techniques
Generate actionable business insights from multi-domain datasets
          Datasets Used
 Groceries Dataset (E-commerce) – Market basket analysis
 Stroke Prediction Dataset (Healthcare) – Classification task
 California Housing Dataset – Regression & clustering
