       Key Results
Random Forest achieved the best classification performance (F1 ≈ 0.99)
XGBoost delivered the highest regression accuracy (R² > 0.80)
K-Means showed the most effective clustering performance
Association rule mining highlighted frequent item patterns but required lower support thresholds for strong rules
 Business Insights
 Retail: Identify top-selling products for promotions and bundling
 Healthcare: Predict stroke risk with high accuracy
 Real Estate: Estimate house prices and segment markets
 Segmentation: Discover customer and geographic clusters
